Text.string: Vault Hunter! I got the fire in my breast and a gun in my hand. We're gonna take back the last Key fragment, and I've figured out where it is! The Jakobs powder cellar!
Over here, Vault Hunter!

Thank you, Lilith. And, Ava... human emotions are well outside of my expertise, but I must state the obvious—Troy Calypso killed Maya. Not Lilith. There is enough fighting going on out there. This may not have been the family you signed up for, but it is the one you have.
Tannis, I... ngh.
She'll figure it out.
So what's the plan, Lilith?
What's the next step, Lilith?
So what now, Lilith?
What's the plan then, Lilith?
Wainwright knows where the final Key fragment is. We go for the Vault. This time, if the Calypsos come, we'll be ready for them.
Wainwright seemed pretty revved up. I can't blame him. Who wouldn't jump at the chance to take back what was stolen from them?
Good luck, Vault Hunter. Don't worry, I got this ship on lockdown, baby!
Let's get a move on!
It's a closet full of color-coded levers and dials! Winny, you didn't tell me we needed to solve an elaborate puzzle!
Nonsense, an elaborate puzzle is its own reward! Vault Hunter, all you have to do is push the request button by that delivery pipe and open the tube near you. We'll solve this puzzle over on our end.
Follow my lead.
Let's see... that's this lever here, crank back the amplitude here...
Winny, hurry. If my sister finds us...
Nope.
Definitely not the right one.
Incorrect.
Definitely not.
Damnation. Alistair, look around for clues!
I am hardly in the mood to... oh, fie, here. “Eagle crab seven wendigo.”
This is the fun part, Alistair! Try and enjoy it. There, the code's in. Vault Hunter, hit the request button. This time for sure!
Super nope.
Still no.
Double incorrect.
Wasn't meant to be.
Winny, will you PLEASE hurry up with this? I do not relish the notion of a confrontation with my sister.
I... you are right, I am sorry. So in that case, I should NOT point out the code written on the ceiling?
What? Aw, damn. “Blue lever, white button, brass chain”—Alistair, you beautiful bastard! This is it! Vault Hunter, press the button!
Got the Grand Reserve!
Got it! The Grand Reserve!
The Grand Reserve!
There's the Grand Reserve!
Wish granted. Hands above your heads, please.
(humms along to animation)
Breathe, Tannis. You can do this.
Let's give it a try. You may want to stand back. As I said, experimental tech.
Yes, it's working! I hope.
Tannis, you all right?
Are you all right, Tannis?
Tannis, are you okay?
You, uh... all right there, Tannis?
Just a little more...
Phaselock outta nowhere!
Hmm. Disconcerting.

Montgomery Jakobs showed me this little side entrance back in my smuggling days. He was a great man, and I owe it to him to see that the Jakobs Corporation gets back in Jakobs hands. Wainwright'll make a damn fine head of the company. Assuming any of us make it out of this alive.
Tannis! Ah, crap.
No! Tannis!
Tannis!
Tannis! Oh, I'm in trouble.
Lilith, the Calypsos just took Tannis!
Lilith, the Calypsos kidnapped Tannis.
Lilith, the Calypsos have kidnapped Tannis.
Lilith, the Calypsos just took Tannis!
Guardians? This makes no sense. There is supposed to be an enormous monster inside a Vault.
Ah. Well. Ask for a monster, get a monster.
Ta da!

Lilith, I understand your concern, but the facts remain. The Calypsos WILL come to feed on the Vault Monster. My presence is required to ensure that WHEN they arrive, their dinner plate will be empty. Trust me, Lilith. It has to be me.
Here we are.
Secret passage behind a waterfall. Classic.
Really? Secret tunnel behind a waterfall?
This passage seems inconvenient. A party trick, perhaps?
Secret waterfall tunnel! Brilliant! Love this gig.
Yeah. Jakobs family loves their secrets. This passage'll put you right underneath the Estate. Stay smooth, operator.
That passage shoulda put you smack dab in the powder cellar! The barrel delivery pipe ain't far. Get movin' and watch your stray shots!
What's a powder cellar?
I'm sorry... powder cellar?
What is a powder cellar?
Great. What's a powder cellar?
I know that. Tannis, I trust you. It's your call.

We use old booze barrels to give every shot from a Jakobs weapon the proprietary aromatic profile our customers trust and love. Every batch is unique. I prefer an oak brandy cask myself—oak takes longer than you think, but it's worth the wait.
This will require a two-pronged attack. Vault Hunter: while you infiltrate the cellar, Alistair and I will slip past the harpy's zealot guard. Tonight, we take back Jakobs.
Hear hear!
The first statue is out there on the terrace. You just have to recreate how the subject died.

This wing of the house's been poorly tended to since even before the harpy got her frigid claws on it. My father considered groundskeepers to be a useless frivolity, like lullabies or birthday parties when all I wanted was a damn clown who could tie BALLOON ANIMALS!||—Yep, sorry, tampin' that one back down now.
Good, you made it. The fragment, Vault Hunter.
We haven't much time. Forgive me, it's a thing I heard someone say once, and I always wanted to try it. Anyway, there's no time for parlor tricks. I will assemble the Vault Key.
You're on your way. That'll take you to the distillery room. You're comin' up on it now.
Vault Hunter, hurry! We've been found!
Nearly done it! Hah, I wish I could see the look on that harpy's face when she finds out!
I trust you know where to put that.
Take care of the Vault Monster. Then, we will eradicate it before the Calypsos arrive.
Well done, Vault Hunter. Now, I've been working on some experimental technology that SHOULD allow us to neutralize the Vault Monster, rendering it useless to the Calypsos.
Ah! Heh! Excellent, it worked. I told Lilith it would. Sir Hammerlock once told me that when hunting a beast, it's best to deny it sustenance. Starving creatures make mistakes.
Aurelia. As your brother, I implore you to stop this.
Step aside, Alistair... while I trim the last loose end of the Jakobs line.
If you want to kill Wainwright, then you will have to—
Yes. I know.
Do what you must, Vault Hunter... There is no saving her.
So... that's what... cold feels like.
Alistair! Alistair, are you all right?
Me, what about you? You were shot just as much as I was!
Oh, I'll be fine. Not the first time I've had lead in my belly! Just have to clench! Hah! Oof.
Thank you, Vault Hunter. For giving her every chance, and... for humoring a blinded fool of a brother.
You two gonna live? You got a little... shot.
You're both looking a bit worse for wear.
Your wounds. Are they dire?
You two aren't about to croak, are you?
We will survive the trip back to the lodge. It's up to you to finish the task, Vault Hunter.
Right. The Vault. To reveal the entrance, you'll have to solve some light statue-based riddles out in the gardens.
Tannis, I don't like this.
Once you clear the path to the Vault, I will join you with the rest of the Vault Key.
Can't you just tell me the answers?
Should we really be solving puzzles right now?
The only puzzles I enjoy are putting skeletons back together after I have removed them from their owners.
You rich folk and your riddles and your puzzles and genuine mourning of dead family members!
Oh! Oh, I do apologize! Are you hearing this, Alistair? The Vault Hunter's lost all whimsical intrigue!
Forgive Winny, he gets cranky when he's been shot. Do just try solving the riddles, Vault Hunter.

That's where my family cask-ages our signature gunpowder! My father must've hidden the fragment in a barrel of Grand Reserve black powder before the Calypsos arrived. Clay knows a secret way to get in. Go and meet up with him.
Now Tyreen Calypso will be unable to derive power from the Vault Monster.

What the actual dick. Did you just kill the Vault Monster for real? Come on! Now there's no point in any of this! Ugh, I'm so hungryyy! I guess I'll... I dunno, leech a pile of tinks? They're like popcorn shrimp, but more... screamy.
You guys really suck, you know that? Totally uncalled for.
That's the founder himself, Singleton Talbot Jakobs. Quite the eye for detail he had, even if it caused him to miss the big picture.
Listen to the recording for a hint.

Singleton was keen with tools, he kept a wrench in pocket, to finely tune the tools of war that caused his sales to rocket. He peered too near at a marksman's gear, and the bullet went right through his socket.
It seems we're alone. You may proceed into the Vault to collect your “loot”. Meanwhile, I will examine the Eridian technology out here.
The man was shot in the face. Didja you catch that part?
Singleton got held up and all he cared to do was inspect the bore of the robber's rifle. That is, until the robber shot him in the face. Head to the menagerie next.

This greenhouse was installed by my grandfather, Wharton. The first Jakobs to sell firearms to someone without a moustache. Man of great vision, and greater greed. It was him that made Jakobs into a galactic name, even if it was just a means of lining his wallet.
Listen to the recordin' for a hint.

Ah, this Vault is indeed connected to the Promethea Vault you opened, as well as... Pandora, and a fourth Vault symbol I do not recognize. Could Tyreen Calypso be telling the truth about the Great Vault? I am concerned. Come out, and we will return to Sanctuary together. Lilith will want to hear about this.
Vault Hunter, we should probably discuss—
Now Ty! Do it, do it, do it!

Wharton tripped in the factory and died of... well, the doctor had to invent a new name for his injury. Called it “fatal testicular devastation” or some such thing. An innovator till the end, my grandpappy was.

This menagerie was installed by my great uncle, Maddox. Maddox didn't trust a soul. The man preferred having bars between him and the rest of the world. He once measured his spaghetti on the suspicion that his cook was short-noodlin' him.
Listen to the recording for a hint.

Wharton waxed his boots and floors to show off his great profit. So burnished was the catwalk that he stepped and slipped right off it. The worst of the falls went right to his balls, the damage was catastrophic.
And she's GONE! Aw, man. When you killed that monster, I was like, “shiiiiit!”, but... we've got our eye on a bigger prize.
The man got hit in the balls so hard he died. You savvy?
Yep, old Maddox spent so much time lookin' out the window he never noticed that his butler was plottin' his demise. Ah, gothic drama! The final riddle is in the greenhouse.
See, you sniffed all those riddles out like a saurian in heat! Head back to the terrace. There'll be a switch to reveal the entrance to the Vault.
See, Winny? The Vault Hunter enjoys solving elaborate puzzles as much as you do.
Yes. Yes, I do suppose the heart of an adventurer still beats within you, Vault Hunter.
I'm adventurous as hell! I've eaten street meats you've never even heard of. Honestly, fry anything and I'll eat it.
Was there ever any doubt? Never question me again.
You are close. I keep one in my jacket pocket.
Not the first time I've punched a statue in the crotch. Won't be the last.
There she is, Vault Hunter. My family legacy. A small price to pay, I think, for bringing the Jakobs Corporation back into its rightful hands. You have my thanks.
Head to the Vault. I will meet you there.
I'm over by the waterfall when you're ready, Vault Hunter.
Alistair and I are nearly to the delivery controls. Vault Hunter, clear the room. We can't let that Key fragment get into zealot hands.
Right on time, Vault Hunter. We're at the controls now.

Vault Hunter. I cannot excuse Aurelia for what she's done to Wainwright and the people of Eden-6. She must answer for her crimes, but she is still my sister. If I could speak with Aurelia, face-to-face, I might convince her to surrender. Enough blood has been shed. And sometimes the bonds of family can be repaired. I ask only for a brother's chance.
Set the dial to “cupcake”, pull the silver chain... and here it comes, Vault Hunter!
I found a stuffed fish with a code on it! That'll be the answer! Alistair, read me the clues and I'll solve it.
Hell's bells! The fish was a red herring! Watch out for more zealots, Vault Hunter!

God damn it, Alistair, my father's dead, my company is in the hands of bandits, and I'm tradin' away my inheritance because I had to save your life! If I have to enjoy myself while solving the last puzzle my father left for me, I damn well shall!
Haha! What'd I tell you? Easy as pie! Key fragment should be right inside.
A team success is what that is! Now we can open the Vault! Come meet me and Alistair near the gardens. I'll open up the way for you. Just follow the conveyor system out of that room.
Maddox was a nervous man who never left his room. The outside world was full of those who surely meant him doom. While his concentration was on ruination, the gun at his back went kaboom.
Sounds like he was shot in the back, doesn't it?
No... damn it! Vault Hunter, I need you back on Sanctuary, now!
It's her choice to go down, Lilith. And we have to do SOMETHING, or the Calypsos get exactly what they want.
